# `.env.example` files document the expected connection-string format.
# They contain placeholder credentials like `<project-ref>` / `<password>`
# but secretlint's connection-string rule matches on structure, not content.
# Real secrets live in `.env` / `.env.local` / AWS Secrets Manager —
# both are gitignored. See CLAUDE.md §"Things Claude Code must NEVER do".
**/.env.example
# `packages/*/prisma.config.ts` contains a placeholder PostgreSQL
# connection string used as fallback when DIRECT_URL env var is not set
# (e.g., during `prisma generate` in CI, which doesn't need a real DB
# connection). The placeholder credentials (`placeholder:placeholder@localhost`)
# are not real secrets. Real DATABASE_URL/DIRECT_URL come from
# AWS Secrets Manager (production) or `.env` (local, gitignored).
packages/*/prisma.config.ts